      <fr:mainmatter>
        <fr:p>From October 2019 until December 2023, I was a PhD student at the University of Cambridge. I started my PhD trying to look at the Adam's Spectral Sequence in HoTT (ambitious, by what I'm given to understand), but life and covid lockdowns happened. I ended up pivoting into interactive theorem proving, thinking about financial smart contracts and their specifications.</fr:p>
        <fr:p>I got into using interactive theorem provers (ITPs)—in particular <fr:link type="external" href="https://rocq-prover.org">Rocq</fr:link>, and <fr:link type="external" href="http://lean-lang.org">Lean</fr:link> more recently—because</fr:p>
        <fr:p>I learned a lot during my PhD.</fr:p>
