          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>I am a mathematician and computer scientist. My <fr:link type="local" href="dhsorens-phd.xml" addr="dhsorens-phd" title="PhD Thesis">PhD</fr:link> was in formal specification of smart contracts in Coq, focusing on the (rather philosophical) problem of ensuring that specifications actually reflect the high-level intentions of their designers. Formal proposition and proof catch my attention in computer science, from various angles.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Here you can see my <fr:link type="local" href="dhsorens-pubs.xml" addr="dhsorens-pubs" title="Peer-Reviewed Publications">publications</fr:link>, <fr:link type="local" href="dhsorens-talks.xml" addr="dhsorens-talks" title="Talks">talks</fr:link>, and <fr:link type="local" href="dhsorens-0003.xml" addr="dhsorens-0003" title="Notes">notes</fr:link>.</fr:p>
